model.common

Class Barcode

  • java.lang.Object
    • model.common.Barcode
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class Barcode
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable
    The Barcode class represents a UPC-A barcode. It holds a 12-number unique integer, and is capable of rendering the graphical representation of the barcode for printing.

    • Method Detail

      • setCode

        public Result setCode(java.lang.String code)
        Accepts a String. For the Barcode to be valid the string must contain only 12 integers. The last integer must be a valid check digit.

      • setCodeFromId

        public Result setCodeFromId(java.lang.String id)
        Accepts a string of integers no longer than 11 characters. A valid barcode based upon the parameter is then generated and set as the code member variable.
